TY  - JOUR
T1  - Competition and the Core
AU  - Telser, Lester G.
Y1  - 1996/02/01
PY  - 1996
DA  - 1996/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/262018
DO  - 10.1086/262018
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 85
EP  - 107
VL  - 104
IS  - 1
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - Core theory is a powerful tool to find competitive market-clearing prices. A familiar economic setting shows this, beginning with a single commodity produced using many factors of production and ending with the general case of many outputs and inputs. The analysis describes when the market has a core. When it has no core, there is a least upper bound on the payment each firm that does not participate in a central market must make that serves as an inducement to restore the core. Since each firm can avoid this penalty by trading in the central market, the result is market-clearing prices that can support an efficient equilibrium.
AB  - Core theory is a powerful tool to find competitive market-clearing prices. A familiar economic setting shows this, beginning with a single commodity produced using many factors of production and ending with the general case of many outputs and inputs. The analysis describes when the market has a core. When it has no core, there is a least upper bound on the payment each firm that does not participate in a central market must make that serves as an inducement to restore the core. Since each firm can avoid this penalty by trading in the central market, the result is market-clearing prices that can support an efficient equilibrium.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/262018
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/262018
Y2  - 2024/03/22
